LAGOS – An economist, Professor Evans Osabuhien, on Mon­day, called on the Federal Government to intensify efforts to reduce the cost of governance in order to achieve sound economic outlook in 2021. Osabuhien, a former Head of Economics De­partment, Covenant Univer­sity, Ota, who spoke in Ota charged the Federal Gov­ernment to take into con­sideration infrastructure development such as road network, stable power sup­ply and adequate security to boost the economy in 2021. Besides, he emphasised the need for government to minimise wastages and cut down the cost of governanc­es to increase production. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! “If all Nigerians have access to the adequate pow­er supply, you can imagine the level of the impacts on Small and Medium Busi­nesses that spur economic activities,” he said. The don, who was not opposed to tax collection, described taxation as an al­ternative means of gener­ating more revenue for the government in the phase of the dwindling oil prices in the international market. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION